This is one of many ways that I am honored to manifest that love, not out of commands nor religious bromides, but because I learned early on that all of humanity is bonded by more similarities than differences.  If love means wanting the very best for others than I can honestly say I love every one.
lenders.occupational_info: I am fortunate to have been self-employed most of my life, which means working hard but loving it because it has given me the time to practice my philosophy of life - which is that the best way to love life is to love many things, because life consists of so many things to see, be and do.  To that end, in my spare time, I have worked in the fields of Social Work, Psychology, Sociology, Acting, Comedy, Song Writing, Music Production and was an Acting Coach at AFI and the Gardner Stage.  I even took off for six months to help a friend with his business, and lived in Manhattan, New York City, during that time, just south of Times Square.  When we begin to think more of others and less of yourselves, we earn more love and respect. When we give more love and respect, we earn more love and respect. It may not always be given what we think is due us, but at least we have earned more self-respect in knowing that we are making the world better, for when we increase the happiness and comfort of one human being or animal, we have increased the world's happiness and comfort in total. That is worthy of love and respect, even if it's only your own when you look in the mirror.
